On Sat, 20 Feb 1999, Jeremy D. Impson wrote:
> Regarding the new 'ip' command:
> 
> I would really like to suggest that instead of deprecating route,
> ifconfig, etc. in favor of ip, we either extend route and ifconfig to
> understand the kernel routing abilities or write a syntax compatibility
> mode for ip so, when called via a symlink to route, it understands route's
> old syntax. 
> 
> Anyone running a heterogenous Unix shop with lots of boxes to admin will
> thank you.
Here here! As with many companies running Linux in a mission-critical
situation, there are a variety of boxes out there, running a variety of
kernels for a variety of reasons. Maintaining some semblance of consitency
between all of them is a Good Thing(tm). :)
